{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-all-timeline-js","path":"/2016/04/24/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"awesomeListRepo":"lukasz-madon/awesome-remote-job","categoryHTML":"<h2>Interviewing</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/andreis/interview\">andreis/interview</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/andreis/interview\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">13.4k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":13393,\"repo\":\"andreis/interview\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Everything you need to kick ass on your coding interview</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T21:56:16.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Contents</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><strong><a href=\"https://github.com/briatte/awesome-network-analysis/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\">Contributing Guidelines</a></strong></li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Conferences</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://conference.polinetworks.org/\">PolNet - Annual Political Networks Workshops and Conference</a> - Organized by the APSA Organized Section on Political Networks (PolNet).\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://vimeo.com/user2690333\">Videos from the Political Networks 2009 Conference</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Conferences</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.netscisociety.net/\">NetSci - International School and Conference on Social Networks</a> - Organized by the Network Science Society (NetSci).\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://danlarremore.com/CommunityDetection_and_Ranking_Larremore_2019.pdf\">Large-scale Structures in Networks: Hidden Communities and Latent Hierarchies</a> - Talk by <a href=\"http://danlarremore.com/\">Dan Larremore</a> at NetSci 2019.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Conferences</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.insna.org/archives.html\">Sunbelt - Social Networks Conference of the International Network for Social Network Analysis</a> - Organized by the International Network for Social Network Analysis (INSNA).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.personal.psu.edu/cxg286/Math485.pdf\">Graph Theory (Mathematics)</a>, by Christopher Griffin - Full lecture notes (Penn State University, 2012).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://tuvalu.santafe.edu/~aaronc/courses/5352/\">Network Analysis and Modeling (Computer Science)</a>, by Aaron Clauset - Full lecture slides and readings (University of Colorado, 2014).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.cc.gatech.edu/~dovrolis/Courses/NetSci/\">Network Science (Computer Science)</a>, by Constantine Dovrolis - Mostly open access readings (Georgia Tech, 2015).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/briatte/parlnet\">Bill Cosponsorship Networks in European Parliaments</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/briatte/parlnet\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">11</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":11,\"repo\":\"briatte/parlnet\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Legislative cosponsorship networks, in R format.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://math.bu.edu/people/kolaczyk/datasets.html\">Eric D. Kolaczyk’s Network Datasets</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://jhfowler.ucsd.edu/cosponsorship.htm\">James H. Fowler’s Cosponsorship Network Data Page</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://moreno.ss.uci.edu/data.html\">Linton Freeman’s Network Data</a> - Over 300 datasets of all sorts, in UCINET format.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://mangal.io/\">Mangal</a> - Online platform to analyze, archive and share ecological network data (<a href=\"http://biorxiv.org/content/early/2015/02/24/002634\">preprint</a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/mangal-wg/pymangal\">Python package</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/mangal-wg/pymangal\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">2</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":2,\"repo\":\"mangal-wg/pymangal\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->, <a href=\"https://github.com/mangal-wg/rmangal\">R package</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/mangal-wg/rmangal\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">11</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":11,\"repo\":\"mangal-wg/rmangal\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www-personal.umich.edu/~mejn/netdata/\">Mark E.J. Newman’s Network Data</a> (<a href=\"http://www-personal.umich.edu/~mejn/networks/\">example visualizations</a>).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://toreopsahl.com/datasets/\">tnet Datasets</a> - Weighted network data.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Professional Groups</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://arshs.hypotheses.org/\">GDR ARSHS - GDR Analyse de réseaux en sciences humaines et sociales</a>, in French - Research group based in Paris.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Professional Groups</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.netscisociety.net/\">NetSci - Network Science Society</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Professional Groups</h2><h3>Research Groups (USA)</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.brighamandwomens.org/research/depts/medicine/channing/default.aspx\">Channing Division of Network Medicine</a> - Research division within the Department of Medicine at Brigham and Women’s Hospital.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Professional Groups</h2><h3>Research Groups (USA)</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://mucha.web.unc.edu/networks/\">Peter J. Mucha’s Research Group at the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Professional Groups</h2><h3>Research Groups (Other)</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.netzwerk-exzellenz.uni-trier.de/\">Forschungscluster der Universitäten Trier und Mainz “Gesellschaftliche Abhängigkeiten und soziale Netzwerke”</a>, in German.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Review Articles</h2><h3>Biological, Ecological and Disease Networks</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0163725813000284\">Structure and Dynamics of Molecular Networks: A Novel Paradigm of Drug Discovery. A Comprehensive Review</a> - Also includes an impressive list of network analysis software (<em>Pharmacology &#x26; Therapeutics</em>, 2013).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Selected Papers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://sociology.stanford.edu/sites/default/files/publications/the_strength_of_weak_ties_and_exch_w-gans.pdf\">The Strength of Weak Ties</a>, by Mark Granovetter - Arch-classic example of applying network analysis to a social issue: jobseeking (<em>American Journal of Sociology</em>, 1973).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://pigale.sourceforge.net/\">PIGALE - Public Implementation of a Graph Algorithm Library and Editor</a> - Windows program and C++ library to analyze planar graphs.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://web.stanford.edu/group/sonia/\">SoNIA - Social Network Image Animator</a> - Tool to visualize dynamic or longitudinal network data. Formerly a <a href=\"https://sourceforge.net/projects/sonia/\">Java program</a> (<a href=\"http://www.soc.duke.edu/~jmoody77/NetMovies/index.htm\">example movies</a>), now developed as the ndtv R package.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/matthewjdenny/CCAS\">CCAS</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/matthewjdenny/CCAS\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">4</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":4,\"repo\":\"matthewjdenny/CCAS\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Statistical model for communication networks.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/aslez/concoR\">concoR</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/aslez/concoR\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">8</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":8,\"repo\":\"aslez/concoR\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Implementation of the CONCOR network blockmodeling algorithm (<a href=\"http://badhessian.org/2015/05/concor-in-r/\">blog post</a>).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/matthewjdenny/ContentStructure\">ContentStructure</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/matthewjdenny/ContentStructure\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">3</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":3,\"repo\":\"matthewjdenny/ContentStructure\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Implements an extension to the <a href=\"http://dirichlet.net/pdf/krafft12topic-partitioned.pdf\">Topic-Partitioned Multinetwork Embeddings (TPME) model</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://people.bu.edu/jccs/spectralGOF.html\">spectralGOF</a> - Computes the spectral goodness of fit (SGOF), a measure of how well a network model explains the structure of an observed network.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>Syntaxes</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://jung.sourceforge.net/\">JUNG - Java Universal Network/Graph Framework</a> - Extensible library to represent network objects.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>Syntaxes</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://tulip.labri.fr/TulipDrupal/?q=tlp-file-format\">TLP - Tulip Software Graph Format</a> - Graph syntax used by the Tulip software framework.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>Syntaxes</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://neo4j.com/docs/stable/cypher-query-lang.html\">Cypher</a> - Graph query language used by <a href=\"http://neo4j.com/\">Neo4j</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>Tutorials</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://curleylab.psych.columbia.edu/netviz/\">Interactive and Dynamic Network Visualization in R</a> and JavaScript libraries (2016).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Varia</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://thesocietypages.org/methods/2015/01/30/david-knoke-on-network-analysis/\">David Knoke on Network Analysis</a> - 20-minute interview that discusses the uses and benefits of network analysis, drawing upon Knoke’s research on terrorist networks.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Varia</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://moreno.ss.uci.edu/pubs.html\">Linton C. Freeman’s Social Network Research Publications</a>, spanning from 1955 to today.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Varia</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://othes.univie.ac.at/12285/1/2010-10-14_0703857.pdf\">Social Network Analysis in DBpedia</a> - Highly didactic Master’s dissertation, showing how to use SPARQL and Pajek.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Varia</h2><h3>Blog Series</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://bactra.org/notebooks\">Cosma R. Shalizi’s Notebooks</a> on network-related topics, definitely worth listing in (selective) detail:\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://bactra.org/notebooks/network-data-analysis.html\">Analysis of Network Data</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://bactra.org/notebooks/neutral-cultural-networks.html\">Assortative Social Networks and Neutral Cultural Evolution</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://bactra.org/notebooks/biochem-network-evol.html\">Biochemical Network Evolution</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://bactra.org/notebooks/citations.html\">Citations and Citation Networks</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://bactra.org/notebooks/community-discovery.html\">Community Discovery Methods for Complex Networks</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://bactra.org/notebooks/complex-networks.html\">Complex Networks</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://bactra.org/notebooks/network-experiments.html\">Experiments on Social Networks</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://bactra.org/notebooks/ergms.html\">Exponential Random Graph Models (ERGMs)</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://bactra.org/notebooks/graph-sampling.html\">Graph Sampling Algorithms</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://bactra.org/notebooks/graph-theory.html\">Graph Theory</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://bactra.org/notebooks/homophily-vs-influence.html\">Homophily and Influence in Social Networks</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://bactra.org/notebooks/inferring-networks.html\">Inferring Networks from Non-Network Data</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://bactra.org/notebooks/text-networks.html\">Joint Modeling of Texts and Networks</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://bactra.org/notebooks/network-comparisons.html\">Network Comparison</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://bactra.org/notebooks/networks-of-political-actors.html\">Networks of Political Actors</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://bactra.org/notebooks/relational-learning.html\">Relational Learning</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://bactra.org/notebooks/social-contagion.html\">Social Contagion, Information Cascades, Diffusion of Innovations, Etc.</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://bactra.org/notebooks/social-networks.html\">Social Networks</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://bactra.org/notebooks/stochastic-block-models.html\">Stochastic Block Models</a>.\n<ul>\n<li>See also: <a href=\"https://www.alexpghayes.com/blog/an-annotated-bibliography-on-stochastic-block-models/\">An Annotated Bibliography on Stochastic Blockmodels</a> (2019).</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Varia</h2><h3>Blog Series</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>Daniel Little’s blog posts on the philosophy of social science:\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://understandingsociety.blogspot.com/search/label/networks\">Networks</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://understandingsociety.blogspot.com/search/label/social%20networks\">Social Networks</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Varia</h2><h3>Blog Series</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>Martin Grandjean’s blog posts about (mostly) network visualization, in English and French:\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.martingrandjean.ch/tag/analyse-de-reseau/\">Network Analysis</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.martingrandjean.ch/tag/reseaux-sociaux/\">Social Networks</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Varia</h2><h3>Blog Series</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>Yannick Rochat’s blog posts about digital humanities, in English and French:\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://yro.ch/tag/character-network/\">Character Networks</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://yro.ch/tag/network-analysis/\">Network Analysis</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Varia</h2><h3>Fictional Networks</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://bokeh.pydata.org/en/latest/docs/gallery/les_mis.html\">Character Co-Occurrences in Victor Hugo’s <em>Les Misérables</em></a>, plotted as an adjacency matrix, written in Python (+ Javascript).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-24T18:35:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Varia</h2><h3>Fictional Networks</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http: